Your `GlobalExceptionHandler` is not being used. The BNPP framework handler is catching it instead:

```text
PfExceptionHandler.handleException
```

So for this test, don’t expect `400`.

Change the test to expect the real framework response:

```java
@Test
void startAuthentication_shouldThrowInternalServerError_whenAppIdMissing() throws Exception {
    mockMvc.perform(get("/auth/start"))
            .andExpect(status().isInternalServerError())
            .andExpect(jsonPath("$.error_description")
                    .value("Internal server error, contact the support with the provided error identifier"));
}
```

Or better: change the controller to throw your framework bad-request exception instead of `IllegalArgumentException`, if your project has one.

For now, for coverage, use the `500` expectation because that matches the actual project behavior.
